[SN]TITLE[SN]
Microlight pilot escapes River Cleddau aircraft crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The pilot of a microlight escaped without serious injury after crashing into the River Cleddau in Pembrokeshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The local coastguard was alerted after the aircraft entered the water near Rudders Boatyard in Burton at about 17:45 GMT on Thursday.
Angle lifeboat said the pilot had managed to swim to shore and was taken to the boatyard by a local boat.
He was treated by paramedics and then taken to Withybush Hospital.
Dyfed-Powys Police, coastguard rescue officers, the port authority and two leisure craft were also in attendance.
The Air Accidents Investigation Branch has been informed of the incident.
